{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015M3vAtkVZuqwLnxxbNCwQE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 4.1: Agent Dispatch Module — SDK Integration\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want an agent-dispatch module that spawns sessions via the Agent SDK,\n11\tso that agent execution is programmatic and reliable.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a compiled `SubagentDefinition` and a prompt string\n16\t   **When** `dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, options)` is called\n17\t   **Then** the Agent SDK `query()` is invoked with the subagent definition, `bare: true`, and the prompt — and the function returns when the session completes\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a successful `dispatchAgent()` call\n21\t   **When** the Agent SDK session completes\n22\t   **Then** the function returns a `DispatchResult` containing `sessionId` (string), `success` (boolean), `durationMs` (number), and `output` (string — the agent's final text response)\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a compiled subagent definition\n26\t   **When** dispatched via `dispatchAgent()`\n27\t   **Then** spawn completes in <5s excluding model response time (NFR3)\n28\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** any `dispatchAgent()` call\n31\t   **When** the Agent SDK is invoked\n32\t   **Then** no `child_process.spawn`, `execFileSync`, or any CLI-based process spawning is used — only the Agent SDK `query()` API (NFR11)\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** an API rate limit error from the Agent SDK\n36\t   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n37\t   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`, the original error message, and the subagent name — no retry logic (that is the engine's responsibility)\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** a network error (timeout, DNS failure, connection refused)\n41\t   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n42\t   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'NETWORK'`, the original error message, and the subagent name\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the Claude CLI binary is not installed or the SDK cannot initialize\n46\t   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n47\t   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'SDK_INIT'`, a descriptive message, and the subagent name\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** an unexpected/unknown error from the Agent SDK\n51\t   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n52\t   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'UNKNOWN'`, the original error stringified, and the subagent name\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t9. **Given** dispatch options include `cwd: '/some/path'`\n56\t   **When** `dispatchAgent()` is called\n57\t   **Then** the Agent SDK `query()` is invoked with `cwd` set to the specified path (used by evaluator for source isolation, story 4-4)\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t10. **Given** unit tests for the agent-dispatch module\n61\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n62\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` covering: successful dispatch, result shape, error classification (rate limit, network, SDK init, unknown), cwd passthrough, bare:true enforcement, no child_process usage, and no regressions in existing tests\n63\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n66\t\n67\t- [x] Task 1: Add `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` dependency (AC: #1, #4)\n68\t  - [x] Run `npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` to add the SDK as a production dependency\n69\t  - [x] Verify the package installs and `query()` is importable\n70\t  - [x] Update `package.json` `files` array if any SDK-related template files are needed (unlikely)\n71\t\n72\t- [x] Task 2: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #1, #2, #5-8)\n73\t  - [x] Define `DispatchOptions` interface: `cwd?: string`, `sessionId?: string` (for story 4-2 continue), `appendSystemPrompt?: string` (for story 4-3 trace IDs)\n74\t  - [x] Define `DispatchResult` interface: `sessionId: string`, `success: boolean`, `durationMs: number`, `output: string`\n75\t  - [x] Define `DispatchError` error class extending `Error` with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT' | 'NETWORK' | 'SDK_INIT' | 'UNKNOWN'`, `agentName: string`, and `cause: unknown`\n76\t  - [x] Import `SubagentDefinition` from `agent-resolver.ts` (the input type)\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 3: Implement `dispatchAgent()` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #9)\n79\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts`\n80\t  - [x] Import Agent SDK `query()` (or equivalent entry point from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`)\n81\t  - [x] Implement `async function dispatchAgent(definition: SubagentDefinition, prompt: string, options?: DispatchOptions): Promise<DispatchResult>`\n82\t  - [x] Pass `bare: true` to the SDK call (always, per AD2)\n83\t  - [x] Pass `cwd` from options if provided\n84\t  - [x] Pass `appendSystemPrompt` from options if provided (for trace ID injection, story 4-3)\n85\t  - [x] Record start time, await SDK completion, compute `durationMs`\n86\t  - [x] Extract `sessionId` and agent output text from SDK response\n87\t  - [x] Return `DispatchResult`\n88\t\n89\t- [x] Task 4: Implement error classification (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8)\n90\t  - [x] Wrap the SDK `query()` call in try/catch\n91\t  - [x] Classify errors by inspecting error type/message/code from the SDK:\n92\t    - Rate limit: HTTP 429 or SDK-specific rate limit error → `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`\n93\t    - Network: ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, fetch errors → `code: 'NETWORK'`\n94\t    - SDK init: binary not found, SDK constructor failure → `code: 'SDK_INIT'`\n95\t    - All other: `code: 'UNKNOWN'`\n96\t  - [x] All errors wrapped in `DispatchError` with original error as `cause`\n97\t\n98\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n99\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`\n100\t  - [x] Mock `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` using vitest `vi.mock`\n101\t  - [x] Test: successful dispatch returns correct `DispatchResult` shape\n102\t  - [x] Test: `bare: true` is always passed to SDK\n103\t  - [x] Test: `cwd` is passed through from options\n104\t  - [x] Test: `appendSystemPrompt` is passed through from options\n105\t  - [x] Test: rate limit error (429) produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`\n106\t  - [x] Test: network error (ECONNREFUSED) produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'NETWORK'`\n107\t  - [x] Test: SDK init failure produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'SDK_INIT'`\n108\t  - [x] Test: unknown error produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'UNKNOWN'`\n109\t  - [x] Test: `durationMs` is a positive number\n110\t  - [x] Test: module does not import `child_process` (grep source file or use static analysis)\n111\t  - [x] Test: no regressions in existing test suite\n112\t\n113\t## Dev Notes\n114\t\n115\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n116\t\n117\tPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-dispatch` calls Agent SDK `query()`, manages sessions, and injects trace IDs (FR19-23). It lives at `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` with tests at `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`. This module is consumed by `workflow-engine` (story 5-1) for task execution and by `evaluator` (story 6-1) for spawning the evaluator agent.\n118\t\n119\t### Agent SDK Integration\n120\t\n121\tThe `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` package provides `query()` as the primary entry point. Key SDK options:\n122\t\n123\t```typescript\n124\t// Conceptual — exact API shape depends on SDK version\n125\timport { query } from '@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk';\n126\t\n127\tconst result = await query({\n128\t  model: definition.model,\n129\t  prompt: prompt,\n130\t  systemPrompt: definition.instructions,\n131\t  appendSystemPrompt: options?.appendSystemPrompt,\n132\t  disallowedTools: definition.disallowedTools,\n133\t  cwd: options?.cwd,\n134\t  bare: true,           // always — per AD2\n135\t});\n136\t```\n137\t\n138\t**Important:** The exact SDK API may differ from what is shown above. The developer MUST check the actual `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` package API when implementing. The key constraint is: use `query()` (or equivalent), pass `bare: true`, and DO NOT use `child_process`.\n139\t\n140\t### Error Classification Strategy\n141\t\n142\tThe SDK may throw different error types. Classification heuristics:\n143\t\n144\t| Signal | Classification |\n145\t|--------|---------------|\n146\t| HTTP 429, \"rate limit\" in message | `RATE_LIMIT` |\n147\t| ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, fetch failure | `NETWORK` |\n148\t| \"claude not found\", \"binary not found\", SDK constructor error | `SDK_INIT` |\n149\t| Everything else | `UNKNOWN` |\n150\t\n151\tNo retry logic in this module. Retry is the engine's responsibility (story 5-1).\n152\t\n153\t### Session Management Extensibility\n154\t\n155\tThis story implements the basic dispatch. Story 4-2 adds session boundary management (fresh vs continue). The `DispatchOptions.sessionId` field is defined here but not actively used — it is a forward-compatible hook for story 4-2. Similarly, `appendSystemPrompt` is defined for story 4-3 (trace ID injection).\n156\t\n157\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n158\t\n159\t- Does NOT implement session boundary management (that's story 4-2)\n160\t- Does NOT generate or inject trace IDs (that's story 4-3)\n161\t- Does NOT create source-isolated workspaces (that's story 4-4)\n162\t- Does NOT implement retry logic (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n163\t- Does NOT parse agent output into structured data (that's evaluator, story 6-2)\n164\t- Does NOT cache subagent definitions (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n165\t- Does NOT manage Docker lifecycle (that's workflow-engine)\n166\t\n167\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n168\t\n169\t- **Do NOT use `child_process.spawn` or `execFileSync`** — NFR11 strictly forbids CLI process spawning\n170\t- **Do NOT implement retry logic** — that's the engine's responsibility\n171\t- **Do NOT cache SDK instances across calls** — each call is independent\n172\t- **Do NOT parse or validate agent output** — return raw text, let consumers (evaluator) parse\n173\t- **Do NOT import from `workflow-state`** — this module has no state awareness\n174\t- **Do NOT set `bare: false`** — always `bare: true` per AD2\n175\t\n176\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n177\t\n178\t- **Story 3-3** created `agent-resolver.ts` with `SubagentDefinition` interface and `compileSubagentDefinition()` — this module imports `SubagentDefinition` as its input type\n179\t- **Story 3-1** created the agent schema — validates configs before they reach this module\n180\t- **Story 3-2** created embedded agent templates — resolved by agent-resolver before reaching this module\n181\t\n182\t### New Dependency\n183\t\n184\tThis story adds the first new runtime dependency since project inception: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`. This must be added to `package.json` `dependencies` (not `devDependencies`) since it is required at runtime.\n185\t\n186\t### Existing Test Patterns\n187\t\n188\tFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n189\t- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n190\t- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n191\t- Mock external dependencies with `vi.mock`\n192\t- Use `vi.fn()` for spying on SDK calls\n193\t- For testing error paths: create mock errors that match SDK error shapes\n194\t- Follow the `agent-resolver.test.ts` pattern for module testing style\n195\t\n196\t### Git Intelligence\n197\t\n198\tRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug -- description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n199\t\n200\t### Project Structure Notes\n201\t\n202\t- New file: `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` — the agent dispatch module\n203\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`\n204\t- Modified file: `package.json` — adds `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` dependency\n205\t- No changes to any existing source files (besides package.json)\n206\t\n207\t### References\n208\t\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 4.1: Agent Dispatch Module — SDK Integration]\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-dispatch]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation]\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns — Enforcement Guidelines]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR19-FR23 — Agent Dispatch FRs]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR3 — Session spawn <5s]\n215\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR11 — Programmatic dispatch only]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — SubagentDefinition interface (input type)]\n217\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md — predecessor story]\n218\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45fbbef5-e9ca-4512-91b9-2760b179ad44","uuid":"6ae69d3a-b05d-42fb-98c3-fdddd72eccfd","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:56:52.543Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration.md","content":"# Story 4.1: Agent Dispatch Module — SDK Integration\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want an agent-dispatch module that spawns sessions via the Agent SDK,\nso that agent execution is programmatic and reliable.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a compiled `SubagentDefinition` and a prompt string\n   **When** `dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, options)` is called\n   **Then** the Agent SDK `query()` is invoked with the subagent definition, `bare: true`, and the prompt — and the function returns when the session completes\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a successful `dispatchAgent()` call\n   **When** the Agent SDK session completes\n   **Then** the function returns a `DispatchResult` containing `sessionId` (string), `success` (boolean), `durationMs` (number), and `output` (string — the agent's final text response)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a compiled subagent definition\n   **When** dispatched via `dispatchAgent()`\n   **Then** spawn completes in <5s excluding model response time (NFR3)\n   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** any `dispatchAgent()` call\n   **When** the Agent SDK is invoked\n   **Then** no `child_process.spawn`, `execFileSync`, or any CLI-based process spawning is used — only the Agent SDK `query()` API (NFR11)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** an API rate limit error from the Agent SDK\n   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`, the original error message, and the subagent name — no retry logic (that is the engine's responsibility)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a network error (timeout, DNS failure, connection refused)\n   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'NETWORK'`, the original error message, and the subagent name\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** the Claude CLI binary is not installed or the SDK cannot initialize\n   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'SDK_INIT'`, a descriptive message, and the subagent name\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** an unexpected/unknown error from the Agent SDK\n   **When** `dispatchAgent()` encounters it\n   **Then** a `DispatchError` is thrown with `code: 'UNKNOWN'`, the original error stringified, and the subagent name\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** dispatch options include `cwd: '/some/path'`\n   **When** `dispatchAgent()` is called\n   **Then** the Agent SDK `query()` is invoked with `cwd` set to the specified path (used by evaluator for source isolation, story 4-4)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** unit tests for the agent-dispatch module\n    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` covering: successful dispatch, result shape, error classification (rate limit, network, SDK init, unknown), cwd passthrough, bare:true enforcement, no child_process usage, and no regressions in existing tests\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Add `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` dependency (AC: #1, #4)\n  - [x] Run `npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` to add the SDK as a production dependency\n  - [x] Verify the package installs and `query()` is importable\n  - [x] Update `package.json` `files` array if any SDK-related template files are needed (unlikely)\n\n- [x] Task 2: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #1, #2, #5-8)\n  - [x] Define `DispatchOptions` interface: `cwd?: string`, `sessionId?: string` (for story 4-2 continue), `appendSystemPrompt?: string` (for story 4-3 trace IDs)\n  - [x] Define `DispatchResult` interface: `sessionId: string`, `success: boolean`, `durationMs: number`, `output: string`\n  - [x] Define `DispatchError` error class extending `Error` with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT' | 'NETWORK' | 'SDK_INIT' | 'UNKNOWN'`, `agentName: string`, and `cause: unknown`\n  - [x] Import `SubagentDefinition` from `agent-resolver.ts` (the input type)\n\n- [x] Task 3: Implement `dispatchAgent()` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #9)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts`\n  - [x] Import Agent SDK `query()` (or equivalent entry point from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`)\n  - [x] Implement `async function dispatchAgent(definition: SubagentDefinition, prompt: string, options?: DispatchOptions): Promise<DispatchResult>`\n  - [x] Pass `bare: true` to the SDK call (always, per AD2)\n  - [x] Pass `cwd` from options if provided\n  - [x] Pass `appendSystemPrompt` from options if provided (for trace ID injection, story 4-3)\n  - [x] Record start time, await SDK completion, compute `durationMs`\n  - [x] Extract `sessionId` and agent output text from SDK response\n  - [x] Return `DispatchResult`\n\n- [x] Task 4: Implement error classification (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8)\n  - [x] Wrap the SDK `query()` call in try/catch\n  - [x] Classify errors by inspecting error type/message/code from the SDK:\n    - Rate limit: HTTP 429 or SDK-specific rate limit error → `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`\n    - Network: ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, fetch errors → `code: 'NETWORK'`\n    - SDK init: binary not found, SDK constructor failure → `code: 'SDK_INIT'`\n    - All other: `code: 'UNKNOWN'`\n  - [x] All errors wrapped in `DispatchError` with original error as `cause`\n\n- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`\n  - [x] Mock `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` using vitest `vi.mock`\n  - [x] Test: successful dispatch returns correct `DispatchResult` shape\n  - [x] Test: `bare: true` is always passed to SDK\n  - [x] Test: `cwd` is passed through from options\n  - [x] Test: `appendSystemPrompt` is passed through from options\n  - [x] Test: rate limit error (429) produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'RATE_LIMIT'`\n  - [x] Test: network error (ECONNREFUSED) produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'NETWORK'`\n  - [x] Test: SDK init failure produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'SDK_INIT'`\n  - [x] Test: unknown error produces `DispatchError` with `code: 'UNKNOWN'`\n  - [x] Test: `durationMs` is a positive number\n  - [x] Test: module does not import `child_process` (grep source file or use static analysis)\n  - [x] Test: no regressions in existing test suite\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Module Location and Architecture Role\n\nPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-dispatch` calls Agent SDK `query()`, manages sessions, and injects trace IDs (FR19-23). It lives at `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` with tests at `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`. This module is consumed by `workflow-engine` (story 5-1) for task execution and by `evaluator` (story 6-1) for spawning the evaluator agent.\n\n### Agent SDK Integration\n\nThe `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` package provides `query()` as the primary entry point. Key SDK options:\n\n```typescript\n// Conceptual — exact API shape depends on SDK version\nimport { query } from '@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk';\n\nconst result = await query({\n  model: definition.model,\n  prompt: prompt,\n  systemPrompt: definition.instructions,\n  appendSystemPrompt: options?.appendSystemPrompt,\n  disallowedTools: definition.disallowedTools,\n  cwd: options?.cwd,\n  bare: true,           // always — per AD2\n});\n```\n\n**Important:** The exact SDK API may differ from what is shown above. The developer MUST check the actual `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` package API when implementing. The key constraint is: use `query()` (or equivalent), pass `bare: true`, and DO NOT use `child_process`.\n\n### Error Classification Strategy\n\nThe SDK may throw different error types. Classification heuristics:\n\n| Signal | Classification |\n|--------|---------------|\n| HTTP 429, \"rate limit\" in message | `RATE_LIMIT` |\n| ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, fetch failure | `NETWORK` |\n| \"claude not found\", \"binary not found\", SDK constructor error | `SDK_INIT` |\n| Everything else | `UNKNOWN` |\n\nNo retry logic in this module. Retry is the engine's responsibility (story 5-1).\n\n### Session Management Extensibility\n\nThis story implements the basic dispatch. Story 4-2 adds session boundary management (fresh vs continue). The `DispatchOptions.sessionId` field is defined here but not actively used — it is a forward-compatible hook for story 4-2. Similarly, `appendSystemPrompt` is defined for story 4-3 (trace ID injection).\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Do\n\n- Does NOT implement session boundary management (that's story 4-2)\n- Does NOT generate or inject trace IDs (that's story 4-3)\n- Does NOT create source-isolated workspaces (that's story 4-4)\n- Does NOT implement retry logic (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n- Does NOT parse agent output into structured data (that's evaluator, story 6-2)\n- Does NOT cache subagent definitions (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n- Does NOT manage Docker lifecycle (that's workflow-engine)\n\n### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n\n- **Do NOT use `child_process.spawn` or `execFileSync`** — NFR11 strictly forbids CLI process spawning\n- **Do NOT implement retry logic** — that's the engine's responsibility\n- **Do NOT cache SDK instances across calls** — each call is independent\n- **Do NOT parse or validate agent output** — return raw text, let consumers (evaluator) parse\n- **Do NOT import from `workflow-state`** — this module has no state awareness\n- **Do NOT set `bare: false`** — always `bare: true` per AD2\n\n### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n\n- **Story 3-3** created `agent-resolver.ts` with `SubagentDefinition` interface and `compileSubagentDefinition()` — this module imports `SubagentDefinition` as its input type\n- **Story 3-1** created the agent schema — validates configs before they reach this module\n- **Story 3-2** created embedded agent templates — resolved by agent-resolver before reaching this module\n\n### New Dependency\n\nThis story adds the first new runtime dependency since project inception: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`. This must be added to `package.json` `dependencies` (not `devDependencies`) since it is required at runtime.\n\n### Existing Test Patterns\n\nFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n- Mock external dependencies with `vi.mock`\n- Use `vi.fn()` for spying on SDK calls\n- For testing error paths: create mock errors that match SDK error shapes\n- Follow the `agent-resolver.test.ts` pattern for module testing style\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug -- description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New file: `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` — the agent dispatch module\n- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`\n- Modified file: `package.json` — adds `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` dependency\n- No changes to any existing source files (besides package.json)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 4.1: Agent Dispatch Module — SDK Integration]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-dispatch]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns — Enforcement Guidelines]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR19-FR23 — Agent Dispatch FRs]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR3 — Session spawn <5s]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR11 — Programmatic dispatch only]\n- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — SubagentDefinition interface (input type)]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md — predecessor story]\n","numLines":218,"startLine":1,"totalLines":218}}}
