{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TcL19NuABCgz9pDg1b9pCR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created. The user asked me not to modify sprint-status.yaml, not to git add, and not to git commit. Done.\n\n---\n\n**Story created:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md`\n\n**Story 4.2: Session Boundary Management** -- ready-for-dev\n\nKey design decisions:\n- New `src/lib/session-manager.ts` module (not modifying agent-dispatch.ts, which is intentionally stateless)\n- 9 acceptance criteria, all tagged `test-provable` (pure logic over in-memory state objects, no running app needed)\n- Session ID lookup via reverse search of `tasks_completed` array in WorkflowState\n- Covers: fresh sessions, continue sessions, fallback to fresh on first invocation, loop iteration behavior, crash recovery, default behavior\n\nThe story leverages existing infrastructure already built in stories 4-1 (DispatchOptions.sessionId), 1-3 (TaskCheckpoint.session_id), and 2-1 (workflow schema session enum).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No problems encountered.** Epic definition was clear and unambiguous for story 4-2.\n- **Workarounds applied:** None.\n- **Risks identified:**\n  - The story creates a new `session-manager.ts` module rather than adding logic directly to `agent-dispatch.ts`. This is intentional per the anti-pattern in story 4-1 (\"Do NOT import from workflow-state\"), but the developer must understand that the workflow-engine (story 5-1) is the orchestrator that ties session-manager + agent-dispatch + workflow-state together. If 5-1 is not implemented correctly, session boundaries won't work end-to-end even though the unit tests pass.\n  - All ACs are `test-provable` because session-manager operates on in-memory WorkflowState objects. True end-to-end session boundary behavior (SDK actually resuming a session) is only testable at integration level in story 5-1.\n- **Observations:**\n  - Story 4-1 already implemented the `resume` passthrough in agent-dispatch.ts (line 135) and defined `DispatchOptions.sessionId`, so this story's scope is narrower than the epic text suggests -- it's primarily about the lookup/persistence logic, not the dispatch mechanics.\n  - The `TaskCheckpoint` in workflow-state.ts already has `session_id?: string`, so no schema changes are needed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 13\n- By tool: Read: 8, Glob: 3, Grep: 1, Bash: 1, Write: 1, Skill: 1 (total including skill invocation: 15)\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 11 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None. Each read targeted a distinct artifact needed for story context."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a54194535e0f2b95d (use SendMessage with to: 'a54194535e0f2b95d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65432\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 134274</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45fbbef5-e9ca-4512-91b9-2760b179ad44","uuid":"67380a24-2edd-44b5-9806-10a400aea12c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T20:12:49.645Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 4-2-session-boundary-management. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. The project is at /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness.\n\nThis is story 4.2 from Epic 4 in the sprint plan. Auto-discover the story details from the epics file and create the story spec.\n\nFor each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database