{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N6moxj4qqjLtwBuA4vgPGH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review complete.** Story 4-2 moved to `verifying`.\n\n**Summary of fixes applied:**\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/session-manager.ts` — 4 fixes: defensive guard for unknown boundary values, input validation on `recordSessionId`, explicit `undefined` check in `getLastSessionId`, corrected docstring\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/session-manager.test.ts` — 3 new tests (25 total, up from 22), all passing\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md` — status changed to `verifying`, review notes appended\n\n**Coverage results:** 96.64% overall, all 155 files above 80% per-file floor. 152 test files, all passing.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- **MEDIUM**: `resolveSessionId` — unknown boundary value fell through to `continue` behavior (should default to `fresh`). Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: `recordSessionId` — no validation on empty `sessionId`, creating silently broken checkpoints. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: `getLastSessionId` — falsy check on `session_id` conflated empty string with undefined. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: Misleading docstring on `recordSessionId` (claimed engine sets `completed_at`, but function did). Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- No module-level JSDoc on `session-manager.ts` (cosmetic)\n- Test helper `makeCheckpoint` always uses same default key values — minor footgun for future test authors\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. 100% coverage on `session-manager.ts`. All files above 80% floor. 96.64% overall.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `recordSessionId` creates full `TaskCheckpoint` entries including `completed_at` timestamp. When story 5-1 implements the workflow engine, there's a risk of the engine also creating checkpoints, producing duplicates. Story 5-1 should use `recordSessionId` as the sole checkpoint creator for session-tracked tasks, or this function should be refactored to annotate existing checkpoints.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): coverage run (~30 lines), git status --porcelain (~25 lines), git diff --name-only (~14 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a28c951ebc9e9a7ff (use SendMessage with to: 'a28c951ebc9e9a7ff' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 47525\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 188717</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45fbbef5-e9ca-4512-91b9-2760b179ad44","uuid":"5336a2b8-37e1-4ed6-b904-63fc0255a257","timestamp":"2026-04-02T20:20:02.295Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `npx codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. The project is at /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness.\n\nThe new files to review are:\n- src/lib/session-manager.ts\n- src/lib/__tests__/session-manager.test.ts\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files b